OL,5,FPoppy's books encouraged her to "look
OL,6,Fat the pictures" or "skip the word"
OL,7,Fwhen she became stuck. But no matter
OL,8,Fhow much she tried to catch up at
OL,9,Fhome, Lisa soon came to the painful
OL,10,Frealisation that her daughter couldn't
OL,11,Fread.
OL,13,FNow 11, Poppy has the reading age of a
OL,14,Ffour-year-old.
OL,16,F"I just worry how will she cope if I
OL,17,Fwasn't here. Who's going to tell her
OL,18,Fhow to read that sign or how to read a
