OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FPoppy is one of the tens of thousands
OL,6,Fof pupils across Wales leaving primary
OL,7,Fschool functionally illiterate. They
OL,8,Fare victims of the fact that methods
OL,9,Fof teaching reading which have been
OL,10,Fdiscredited for decades are still
OL,11,Fencouraged by the Welsh government.
OL,13,FIn this method, children are told to
OL,14,Fuse pictures and context to tackle
OL,15,Funfamiliar words. This technique has
OL,16,Fbeen proven to damage the ability of
OL,17,Fmany young children to learn to read.
