OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FUnlike the rest of the UK, Welsh
OL,6,Fchildren don't take part in the
OL,7,Finternational primary reading test
OL,8,Fknown as PIRLS, and there is no
OL,9,Fnational test data. But, in 2012, the
OL,10,Fschools' watchdog, Estyn, said that a
OL,11,Ffifth of children were starting
OL,12,Fsecondary school "functionally
OL,13,Filliterate".
OL,15,FThe effects of illiteracy can be
OL,16,Fdevastating. Studies have found that
OL,17,Fpeople who are unable to read are more
OL,18,Flikely to suffer from mental health
OL,19,Fproblems, go to prison and die younger.
OL,21,FThe problem
