OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FBut neither of these things are true.
OL,6,FLearning to read does not come
OL,7,Fnaturally, and half a century ago eye
OL,8,Fmovement studies proved that the best
OL,9,Freaders process all the letters in a
OL,10,Fword, it just happens so quickly they
OL,11,Fdon't notice.
OL,13,FIt is in fact the worst readers who
OL,14,Fdepend most on context.
OL,16,FHundreds of studies have shown that
OL,17,Fyoung children need explicit
OL,18,Finstruction in how the letters they
OL,19,Fsee on the page connect to the sounds
OL,20,Fthey make. This is known as phonics.
