OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FReading scientists say that the cueing
OL,6,Fmethods found in Welsh classrooms lead
OL,7,Fto children guessing words rather than
OL,8,Fsounding them out. These kids tend to
OL,9,Fread the first couple of letters of a
OL,10,Fword and guess the rest, a habit that
OL,11,Fbecomes increasingly hard to break as
OL,12,Fthey get to trickier texts.
OL,14,F"Cueing is not based on any empirical
OL,15,Fevidence of how children learn to
OL,16,Fread, it's just a wish list," says
OL,17,FProfessor Emerita Rhona Stainthorp
OL,18,FOBE, one of the UK's leading experts
OL,19,Fon reading development.
OL,26,@vD@AOUxD@]O]
