OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,F"All the evidence from masses of work
OL,6,Fin America, Australia and the UK, is
OL,7,Fthat you must teach young children to
OL,8,Fread the words. The pictures might be
OL,9,Fnice and pretty, but they don't help
OL,10,Fyou to read."
OL,12,FSome children will learn to read
OL,13,Fhowever they are taught, but many will
OL,14,Ffail without explicit teaching.
OL,15,FAdvocates of systematic synthetic
OL,16,Fphonics say that as it is impossible
OL,17,Fto predict which children will
OL,18,Fstruggle, explicitly teaching all
OL,19,Fchildren phonics is vital.
