OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FWe shared our findings with Professor
OL,6,FEmerita Stainthorp, including one
OL,7,FEstyn report from this year which
OL,8,Fpraised a school for encouraging the
OL,9,Fuse of "a range of strategies" to read
OL,10,Funfamiliar words, including "picture
OL,11,Fcues".
OL,13,F"I'm speechless. I really am
OL,14,Fspeechless," she said. "I think that
OL,15,Fis unbelievably awful. It suggests
OL,16,Fthat they haven't got any skills to
OL,17,Fread the unfamiliar words themselves.
OL,18,FBecause if you've got the skills to
OL,19,Fdecode unfamiliar words, you don't
OL,20,Fneed a picture."
