OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,F"Using cueing undermines this
OL,6,Fprocess," Gareth Rein, Headteacher of
OL,7,FSt Peter's R.C. School says, "as a
OL,8,Fchild is led to believe that
OL,9,Fcontextual clues are a fix" for not
OL,10,Fbeing able to properly sound out the
OL,11,Fwhole word.
OL,13,FScientists have also found that using
OL,14,Fboth methods can overload the
OL,15,Fcognitive abilities of very young
OL,16,Fchildren. The pictures, for example,
OL,17,Fdistract kids from the words, harming
OL,18,Ftheir ability to read text in the long
OL,19,Fterm.
