OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FExperts are keen to stress that
OL,6,Fenjoying pictures with children is not
OL,7,Fa problem, but that encouraging
OL,8,Fchildren to try and guess unfamiliar
OL,9,Fwords by using the pictures should be
OL,10,Favoided.
OL,12,F"It is essential," says Christopher
OL,13,FSuch, "that they are not discouraged
OL,14,Ffrom first looking at all the letters
OL,15,Fwithin the word and considering the
OL,16,Frelated sounds to try to work out what
OL,17,Fthe word might be."
