OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FThere is concern that the poorest
OL,6,Fchildren and those with learning
OL,7,Fdifficulties are harmed the most by
OL,8,Fcueing strategies.
OL,10,FChildren who are already good readers
OL,11,Fimprove more quickly than their
OL,12,Fclassmates, while poor readers fall
OL,13,Ffurther behind. This phenomenon is
OL,14,Fexacerbated as those struggling get
OL,15,Fincreasingly frustrated and avoid
OL,16,Freading entirely.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G21/32
