OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,F"It's pretty intuitive," Christopher
OL,6,FSuch tells me, "it's hard to get a kid
OL,7,Fto love football if they fall over
OL,8,Fevery time they kick the ball. It's
OL,9,Fhard to get a kid to love reading if
OL,10,Fthey can't actually make meaning from
OL,11,Fthe text because they can't recognise
OL,12,Fthe words on the page."
OL,14,FNational test data released by the
OL,15,FWelsh government this summer showed
OL,16,Fthat by the time they reach Year 9,
OL,17,Fthe average English reading levels of
OL,18,Fchildren from poorer households are
OL,19,Fnow two and a half years behind their
OL,20,Fpeers.
