OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FThe result, say teachers, is that tens
OL,6,Fof thousands of Wales' most
OL,7,Fdisadvantaged children can't read when
OL,8,Fthey leave primary school.
OL,10,F"We just have a widening attainment
OL,11,Fgap as a result of these poor reading
OL,12,Fstrategies being taught in our
OL,13,Fschools," says Rob Randel, a primary
OL,14,Fschool teacher in Wales of two
OL,15,Fdecades, and member of the Reading
OL,16,FReform Foundation.
OL,18,F"We are just completely letting down
OL,19,Four children at the moment by
OL,20,Fcontinuing to use these discredited
OL,21,Fapproaches."
OL,26,@rD@AOUuD@IO]zD@AOU}D@LO]
