OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FTaking matters into their own hands
OL,7,FParents and schools are beginning to
OL,8,Fignore Welsh government guidance.
OL,10,FTracy, from the Neath Valley, told me
OL,11,Fthat when she raised concerns with her
OL,12,Fson's school that he couldn't read the
OL,13,Fletters confidently, she was told that
OL,14,F"boys are slower than girls" and "not
OL,15,Fto worry" as he would "get it in his
OL,16,Fown time."
OL,18,FTracy decided to buy a phonics set
OL,19,Fonline and taught him how to sound the
OL,20,Fwords out herself.
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@\O]vD@bOUwD@IO]wD@WOUxD@JO]
