OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,F"We used to do it every morning before
OL,6,Fschool... within two years, he was
OL,7,Freading Harry Potter books
OL,8,Fconfidently. I'm confident that
OL,9,Fwouldn't have been possible if we'd
OL,10,Fcontinued with the school's learning
OL,11,Ftrajectory."
OL,13,FAnother mum from Carmarthenshire, who
OL,14,Fdidn't want to be named, has resorted
OL,15,Fto teaching her daughter a phonics
OL,16,Fprogramme at home.
OL,18,F"I found out that my daughter wasn't
OL,19,Fhaving explicit phonics lessons at
OL,20,Fschool," she said.
