OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FAs a former primary school teacher,
OL,6,Fshe said she was "fortunate" she had
OL,7,Fthe knowledge and resources to buy the
OL,8,Fprogramme and teach it. "Many parents
OL,9,Fcannot do this and it really shouldn't
OL,10,Fbe their responsibility in the first
OL,11,Fplace."
OL,13,FA small minority of schools are also
OL,14,Ftaking things into their own hands. At
OL,15,FSt Peter's R.C. School in the centre
OL,16,Fof Cardiff, results have improved
OL,17,Fsignificantly since teachers stopped
OL,18,Fusing cueing methods.
