OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FThe average reading age of a child
OL,6,Ffrom St Peter's moving to secondary
OL,7,Fschool last year was 13 years and
OL,8,Fseven months.
OL,10,F"This provides them with a head start
OL,11,Fin Year 7 and will likely be the
OL,12,Ffoundation for achieving academic
OL,13,Fsuccess later on," headteacher Gareth
OL,14,FRein tells me.
OL,16,F"When the schools in which I have
OL,17,Fworked have moved away from multi-
OL,18,Fcueing...greater numbers of children
OL,19,Fhave achieved success.
