OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FIn Twynyrodyn Primary School in
OL,6,FMerthyr Tydfil, teachers also follow a
OL,7,Fsystematic synthetic phonics programme
OL,8,Fand do not use cueing to teach reading
OL,9,Fin early years.
OL,11,FHeadteacher Alec Mills told me that
OL,12,Fsince adopting this approach, reading
OL,13,Flevels have improved markedly,
OL,14,Fespecially for the most disadvantaged
OL,15,Flearners.
OL,17,F"Our outcomes are much stronger than
OL,18,Fthey were. It has been really
OL,19,Feffective in ensuring that all our
OL,20,Fchildren maintain pace with their
OL,21,Fpeers."
OL,26,@yD@AOU}D@GO]
