OL,3,CInside Wales' reading crisis
OL,5,FMr Mills said that teaching reading
OL,6,Fusing systematic synthetic phonics
OL,7,F"will change the lives" of his pupils.
OL,9,F"They are going to leave here with
OL,10,Fsuch a key literacy skill unlocked for
OL,11,Fthem that whatever their aspirations
OL,12,Fare for life, reading isn't going to
OL,13,Fbe the thing that holds them back, and
OL,14,Fwe're really proud of that."
OL,16,FWhat does the Welsh Government say?
OL,18,FWe asked to speak to the Welsh
OL,19,FGovernment's Cabinet Secretary for
OL,20,FEducation Lynne Neagle about this
OL,21,Fstory multiple times, but she refused.
